            . I am a constable. I stopped the prisoner upon another indictment. This pint pot was in this bag, I found this bag upon him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120408-24-person250">
                  ROBERT 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18120408-24-person250" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120408-24-person250" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120408-24-person250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner coming out of the public-house, the Three Butts at the corner of the Old Jewry with a pot under his coat; I followed him to Basinghall-street and stopped him; the constable coming by asked me if I was a constable: I said, no, he said he would take charge of him; he did. Afterwards we found this other pot in the bag.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. This is my pot. The prisoner has been in the habit of coming to the house for some time. When I saw him at the Compter I said to him, I am sorry to see you here; I thought he was a carpenter. He said he stole the pot from my house.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence I met an old shipmate that day he gave me some liquor; I did not know rightly what I was doing off.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18120408-24-verdict146" type="verdictDescription">
